-8 |oclc=30320648 |ref=harv }}\n* {{cite book |last=Dick |first=C. J. |title=From Victory to Stalemate - Decisive and Indecisive Military Operations, Volume 1 |location=Lawrence, Kansas |publisher=University Press of Kansas |year=2016 |isbn=978-0-7006-2293-1 |oclc=1023039366 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal |last=Goodfriend |first=Arthur |title=Battle in the Snow |journal=Infantry Journal |date=May 1946 |volume=58 |issue=5 |pp=28\u201334 |url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=j3_pAAAAMAAJ&pg=RA4-PA33 |ref=harv }}\n* {{cite book |last=Harrison |first=Gordon A. |title=Cross Channel Attack |series = United States Army in World War II \u2013 The European Theater of Operations |location=Washington, DC |publisher=Office of the Chief of Military History, Department of the Army |year=1951 |oclc=78600975 |url=https://history.army.mil/html/books/007/7-4-1/CMH_Pub_7-4-1.pdf |ref=harv }}\n* {{cite book |last=Hogan |first=David W., Jr. |title=A Command Post at War: First Army Headquarters in Europe 1943\u20131945 |publisher=US Government Printing Office |location=Washington DC |year=2000 |url=https://history.army.mil/html/books/070/70-60/CMH_Pub_70-60.pdf |access-date=26 January 2020 |id=CMH Pub 70-60 |isbn=0-16-049771-X |oclc=43662157 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite document |last=Mack |first=Harold L. |title=The Critical Error of World War II |publisher=National Defense University |location=Washington, D.C. |date=February 1981 |series=National Security Affairs Issue Paper |hdl=2027/uiug.30112074912624 |id=81-1 |oclc=605367568 |ref=harv }}\n* {{cite book |last=Mayo |first=Lida |title=The Ordnance Department: On Beachhead and Battlefront |series = United States Army in World War II \u2013 The Technical Services |location=Washington, D.C. |publisher=Office of the Chief of Military History, Department of the Army |year=1968 |url=http://www.history.army.mil/html/books/010/10-11/CMH_Pub_10-11.pdf |accessdate=20 October 2015 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Millett |first=J. D. |title=The Orga